	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Aug 21st 5:10 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well here's some news for people who don't try things for themselves. The 4 focus items from the Temple of Solusek Ro work for pets from level 4 to level 49. Not from 34 up. Here's 2 reasons. First of all get a nice resource file browser like EQInside or EQCaster. Go to the pet summons and notice all summons from 4 to 49 allow the use of the basic focus items. Second, I tested it in game. Below level 34 your pets size does not increase. It just has a higher damage cap. At level 32, if I use the level 24 earth pet I can summon a green pet that has max damage from 16 to 22 or a blue pet with a max of 24. If I use the focus item the blue pet now does 26. And I can now get a green pet that does 24. Pets that are level 49 summons and above work with the staffs of elemental mastery: the high level focus items. Level 49 pets can be buffed with either the basic or high level focus items. Pets above level 50 are only affected by the staffs. Also, focus items DO NOT increase level or max level that you can summon. The Verant people have said this over and over and it just isn't true. I found that with the level 24 earth pet and the level 29 fire and water pets, I never got more blues. It just increased the max damage.<br><br>Enokhaon Starfyre<br>Mage of the 32nd Circle<br>Aven du Sora Guild<br>Innoruuk Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
