<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=9678048173971></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f9678048173971><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9678048173971>RE: Focus Items</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=9678048173971#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=887><span id=Sage>Zuranthium</span></a>, <span id=Sage>Sage</span><br><span id=notbold>390 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Sep 1st 6:40 AM 2000</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.55]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>It doesn't matter what level your pet is. Its how powerful they are in correspondence to that level. Levels really don't mean anything at higher levels, becuase MOBS have varying degree's of power. Look at a level 35 spector. Low hp and fairly weak melee (although they do stun a bit more than usuall). Now look at a level 35 uber-guard. They are doing MASSIVE damage(up to 180's), and they still have just as much hp as that spector. Just becuase something is higher or lower level then something else it doesn't mean its more powerful/weaker than something else. Another example would be giant snakes and orc centurions in east commons. Level 9 Giant snakes do up to 20 a hit, don't bash, and have the regular hp for their level. A level 9 centurion does up to 22 a hit, bashes, and a has a lot more hp than that snake. Focus items makes your pets more powerful, not increase their level.<br><br>Zuranthium/Divineshadow/Corpusnuntia/Plantmaster/Naltec/Natalos/Sunsong<br><br>Player of many characters on the Nameless server.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
