	   <tr><td colspan=2>Have you tried having others con your pet when you summon one with and without a focus item?....&nbsp;&nbsp;Cause dmg is capped on the level of the pet just as dammage is capped for pc's and increases at lvl 10, 20, and so on.<br><br>I'm sure everyone agrees that if you summon a green pet and a blue pet, the blue will do more dmg.  Therefore level of pet =  max dmg it does.<br><br>Even your post states "If I use the focus item the blue pet now does 26. And I can now get a green pet that does 24", that means the focus item gives you a better chance of summoning higher level pets that do more dmg.  The focus do not affect the dmg as stated but they do affect the level of the pet summoned which affects dmg.<br><br>Also if you summon more blues using the focus items, then it must affect the level of the pet.<br><br>Show me a post from gordon or abashi where focus items do not affect the level of the pet.<br><br>The size of the pet does change when using a focus item.  However the max pet size is still pre-determined by the level of the pet spell.<br><br>A lvl 24 or 29 pet spell wouldnt have a big size difference between  focus or non-focus summoned pet.   A lvl 39+ spell will.   My lvl 44 pet is puny without the shovel and twice as big with the shovel.<br><br>Also according to most people the shovel increases the size of the pet  only until level 34 when the stat buffs kick in.  The effect on the focus items isnt supposed to give level/stat boosts until 34.<br><br>The size of the pet does change lvl 34- spells but not a big difference.<br>&nbsp;<br>Eendyar Soulseeker<br>46'th High Elf Mage <br>"Mythic Synergy"<br><a href="http://www.mythicsynergy.com" target=_new>http://www.mythicsynergy.com</a><br>Fennin Ro</td></tr>
